We should test `repo->first == record` first right? As it is not expensive at all, unlike `pldm_pdr_get_prev_record()` which is `O(N)` wrt the repository size.

so:

```
if (repo->first == record) {
    return true;
}

return pldm_pdr_get_prev_record(repo, record) != NULL;
```

Given we're skipping it we can avoid testing the result, but we do need to test the result of the `hdr_type` extraction below. So this could instead look like:

```
pldm_msgbuf_span_required(dst, skip_data_size, NULL);
if ((rc = pldm_msgbuf_extract(dst, hdr_type))) {
   return rc;
}
```

That should save the awkward wrapping of the `NULL` parameter.
